 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Teaching Faculty Nexford University Washington, DC Remote Job details Salary $50,000 - $55,000 a year Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Nexford University (NXU) is seeking a Teaching Faculty member with expertise in business and technology fields, including but not limited to Finance, Accounting, Supply Chain Management, Artificial Intelligence/Machine Learning, Cyber Security, Big Data Analytics, Cloud Computing, IoT, Marketing, Economics, Entrepreneurship/Intrapreneurship, Management, Human Resources, Leadership, and/or International Business. The Teaching Faculty will support the overall mission of Nexford to bring high-quality, affordable, dynamic education that prepares learners for the global workplace. 
 
 
Under the general direction of the Dean of Business, this role will have the opportunity to influence and shape the future of learning. The Teaching Faculty will support learner success by ensuring the quality of NXUâ€™s undergraduate and graduate curriculum and delivery. 
Key responsibilities 
 
 
The Teaching Faculty should motivate learners to actively engage in all aspects of their educational journey and focus on the commitment to learner success. The Teaching Faculty:
 Manages online courses through the Learning Management System (LMS) and other innovative technology tools 
 Interacts with learners online via discussion, chat, virtual office hours, live engagements, and emails
 Teaches and facilitates the course(s), as designed, in an efficient and engaging manner 
 Engages in course(s) at least three (3) times per week 
 Provides personalized and substantive feedback on learner submissions and other assignments within five (5) days of submission date 
 Actively responds to learner emails, phone calls, and messages within 24 hours 
 Mentors learners on course content and skill development that expands the learner experience with insights, unique personal experiences, professional applications and other practical/conceptual knowledge and expertise 
 Posts updates and announcements to course(s) regularly to support learner learning 
 Participates in NXU webinars, blogs, and marketing campaigns, as applicable
 Provides feedback and recommendations on course content to ensure high quality and relevant delivery of information
 Remains current in his/her academic program or discipline, attending conferences and maintaining any licensure or continuing education requirements 
 Participates in departmental and university affairs as requested 
 Adheres to all NXU faculty expectations 
 Performs other duties as assigned 
Required Skills and Qualities 
 
Has a clear vision for education and commitment to excellence using an innovative practical approach 
 Track record for making data-driven decisions that constantly improve instructional delivery 
 An advocate for and promoter of quality curriculum utilizing high levels of engagement, and with a high commitment to learner success that is fully aligned with workplace requirements 
 Flexible work style appropriate for remote and international team collaboration 
 Sound judgment and decision-making skills appropriate for NXUâ€™s fast-paced, entrepreneurial culture 
 Technology savviness, fluent using social media channels, learning management systems, and other new and innovative technology systems that support an enriching learning experience 
 Outstanding communication skills and polished presentation style 
 Strong outcomes-based orientation and track record for achieving results 
 Progressive mindset that promotes a next-generation experience serving the unique needs of the future of work. 
Required Experience 
 
2-3 years of teaching experience in a Business School or Department of an accredited institution; online teaching experience is required. 
 4-7 years of industry experience highly desired 
 Faculty experience in undergraduate and graduate Business programs, online preferred 
 Experience in developing innovative curriculum and assessments (Competency-Based Education preferred) 
 
 
Preferences 
 
3+ years of industry experience, particularly in a leadership role 
 Experience with Competency-Based Education (CBE) 
 1+ years of online teaching experience 
Application Instructions 
For full consideration, an application should include a cover letter, resume/CV, teaching philosophy, and unofficial transcripts. 
Compensation and Benefits 
 
Work at a company with a social mission where you can make a real difference in the world 
 20 days paid time off 
 12 paid days professional development time off, after 3 months of employment 
 Healthcare 
 401K 
 
 50% discounted tuition on all Nexford courses for your family 
 
 A friendly global team 
 Contemporary collaboration tools 
 An entrepreneurial and highly stimulating environment 
 An environment where you will be technically and intellectually challenged 
 100% remote work 
 Free access to LinkedIn Learning from Day 1. 
 
 
This position classification has been defined as exempt and is not subject to the overtime provisions of the Fair Labor Standards Act (FLSA). 
About Nexford University 
Nexford University is a next-generation university based in Washington DC offering a competency-based learning model. Nexfordâ€™s mission is to enable greater social and economic mobility by providing an affordable high-quality education that will positively impact millions of lives around the world. 
Nexford offers the following degrees and certificates: Associate of Applied Science in Business (AAS), Bachelor of Business Administration (BBA), MBA, nine undergraduate certificates and three graduate certificates in the field of business. Nexford provides learners with a fully online global education based on mastery of competencies relevant in the workplace. A global team of faculty and advisors support learning and professional success through the innovative use of technology, such as AI and machine learning. 
For more information, visit www.nexford.org. 
